reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-665-good65-61%-poor60-56%-awful1. HEMANIMAL, HEIDENREICH & CHRISTY HEME vs. MNM- This was a okay tga match to kick off the show. I would say that this was not a good match as it was basically a 2 minute squash and u cant expect more than that when you have a man like lasheys size go up against simon dean. He looked inpressive excpet at the end he messed up the dominator. THe segments after were dean had to eat 20 hamburgers was funny. Winner bobby lashey. Match Rating 3/10.3. CHRIS BENOIT vs. Booker T vs. Christian vs. Orlando Jordan for the wwe us title- This was a good match. All of these guys did a good job including orlando who is usually waful. A nice place for this on the card and really shows all of the talent in the mid card for smackdown. Alot of the action was between beniot and bookerbut lots of fast paced action and a soild match. WInner and still wwe us champ chris beniot. Match Rating 8/10.4. KEN KENNEDY vs. Hardcore Holly- This was also mr kenndys ppv debut. Not as much of a squash match as lasheys was but still very predictable. I think kenndy looked a little better only becuase he got a little more time and his oppent was a little better. Okay match and just passable but a good fit on this card as a filler. WInner  KEN KENNEDY. MAtch Rating 4.5/10.5. Jbl vs. Rey Mysterio- this was a good match. Resembled more of big man vs litttle man action. I was hoping for a litttle more out of these two but this was okay. Jbl controlled alot of this match but than rey fought back with alot of high flying action. Ended out of knowwere but i liked this match. WInner JBL. Match Rating 7/10.6.  Undertaker vs. Randy orton and bob orton in a casket match- This in my opion was match of the night but there were alot of others really close to it. This was given the right amount of time at 18 minutes of soild action aand believe it or not i did not think the bob orton slowed down this match. There were some wepaons used including a fire estiger and a chair. A really sick chair shot at the end of the match that puts taker in the casket. Nice after math. WInner Randy orton and bob Orton. Match Rating 8.5/10.7. NUNZIO vs. JUVETUD GUERRERA for the wwe crusierwieght title- This was a nice was to filler up the card but at the same time ai really enjoyed this match. JUVETUD as champ was awsome uintill he blew it and got in troubl agian. ANway there was alot of fast paced action and when u give them 7 minutes they deliver. WInner and new wwe crusierwieght champ JUVETUD GUERRERA. Match RAting 7/10.8. Batistia vs. Eddie Guerrero for the WHT-  Interesting match & definitely worth a watch. I personally don't think it quite came off, but I could see why some people might have really liked the bout. 19 minutes in length, the entire duration of the match was methodically paced. It was for a reason though, as both men did well in telling a story. To that effect, I commend the WWE for the rather brave booking & also the 2 men for their performances. But the inability to change gears at any stage of the bout hampered it. As did the weak ref bump, the over-selling of Eddie's refusal to cheat & the anti-climactic ending (I think the Batista Bomb was required). The door is now well & truly open for what could be a fascinating rematch. And against my initial reaction, this storyline may indeed work. WInner and still WHc Batistia. Match Rating 8/10.Well that raps up another. I owuld give no mercy 2005 a grade of 52.5/80 which is a 66% whcih means this is a good ppv. This was alright it had its ups and downs but i would try and get it at walmart or off ebay for a cheaper price. If u can tell me if my review was helpful or not i would appreicate that. Thanks for your time.
summary: No mercy 2005 is a 3 star ppv

reviewText: My Review for No Mercy 2005LOD w/Christy Hemme v. MNM w/Melina **Fun opening match with some decent spots. Now I KNOW Christy Hemme loves her job but she's gotta stop smiling the entire time. There are some sloppy points with this but for the most part, much like the Great American Bash encounter, this match is primarily meant to be fun and pop the crowd for the rest of the show. It did it's job.Simon Dean v. Bobby Lashley *3/4A squash match with a ton of botched spots. Lashley has all the tools to be a major star in the WWE but No Mercy wasn't the best start for him. His nervousness showed though big time. Thankfully, WWE was smart enough to give this a funny little side story with the cheeseburgers. Dean's gimmick is really beginning to grow on me. Again a sub par debut for Lashley but overall entertaining enough that I wasn't completely lost.United States Championship--Fatal Four WayChris Benoit v. Christian v. Booker T v. Orlando Jordan **3/4I'm not big on multi man matches but this match was entertaining, but like the previous two matches on the show, not all that good. Lots of fun spots sprinkled throughout and yet again, Chris Benoit retains his title. Nice to see some of the big guns all taking aim at the US title which is in sore need of restored credibility.Mr. Kennedy v. Hardcore Holly **3/4Am I the only one who thought this was a VERY good match for these two? Or is it everyone else so used to crapping on Bob Holly that they do it impulsively? I enjoyed this match even though it wasn't very long. Good back work and outstanding psychology from Kennedy and Holly, both playing up their 'strong' personalities and it being a one upsmanship kind of thing in terms of who could wipe out who more.. Good match and sorely underrated in my opinion.JBL v. Rey Mysterio ***1/2This was a quality match as far as I was conscerned. Generic big man little man on some levels, but played up so incredibly well with Mysterio looking every bit the equal of JBL. JBL kept up enough with Mysterio to make this a quality match that I think will get lost in the shuffle down the line. This is a decent little match.Handicapped Casket matchThe Ortons v. The Undertaker ***1/4This is probobly the best match of their series thus far. These two just have insanely good chemistry. Orton looked every bit like the top heel he's destined to be and Taker looks every bit as indestructable as he should look. Even Bob Sr. carries himself adequetely enough to not detract from the match. Sick chair shot in the end and a great sports entertainment finish to cap it off with Orton getting a serious rub from the deadman.WWE Cruserweight ChampionshipNunzio v. Juventud **1/4Nothing ultra special but a decent short match with the CW belt being hot shotted one more time for good measure. Hopefully they'd keep it on Juvey, but no, it was back on Nunzio in a little over a month. Same drawn out CW crap we see every week. If you want CW action, go watch TNA.World Heavyweight ChampionshipBatista v. Eddie Guererro ***This was Eddie's last pay per view match and it was a decent one, but much like his life, seemed incomplete. This program had SO MUCH going for it and this was merely the setup match to something bigger at Survivor Series. Guererro played the tweener SO INCREDIBLY well. A good match that Eddie did carry but not TOO much. Batista's psychology has improved leaps and bounds. Good match but it will leave you feeling like something was left out, and sadly, we won't ever know what that was.Overall- C+: Much better than people give it credit for in my opinion. Take out a few of the last minute matches, and you've got yourself a pretty darn good show that doesn't have anything that really stands out, but isn't bad either.
summary: Better than it probobly gets credit for...

reviewText: This PPV will primarily be remembered as Eddie Guerrero's last. Unfortunately he delivers a lackluster main event on a lackluster show. His match with Batista never got off the ground, and as cute as the friend/not friends angle was it did nothing to enhance the match. Many people will point out that as WWE champion Guerrero was a financial failure and seemed to crack under pressure, but at least he became champion. Who would have really thought that he would ever attain those heights back when he was in ECW and WCW? And in the ring he will always be considered a legend. Anybody who has not yet seen his matches with Dean Malenko in ECW should really check those out.For me, the Casket Match that pitted the Undertaker vs. Randy Orton and Bob Orton was much more useful than the main event. This is especially surprising considering that the match involves two senior citizens. The first  of the match is as slow as you would expect it to be, but the ending had virtuoso booking that actually had me guessing (and I've been a wrestling fan for 17 years). In the end the casket was set on fire with the Undertaker "inside." While that angle is totally played out it did give the Undertaker another opportunity to take an extended vacation. As we learned ten years ago from the Hukster, when you get to be the Undertaker's age your feet don't leave the ground.My favorite match of the night was Rey Mysterio Jr. vs. JBL. I was against the JBL title reign just like every other self-respecting wrestling fan, but I am now ready to admit that that reign may have done him a boatload of good, wrestling wise. It's still my contention that McMahon gave JBL the title simply to rile up the smart/internet fans. You can make the average fan hate anybody. But it took JBL's lack of wrestling skills, lack of charisma, and lack of street cred to take internet hatred to a new level. Still his match on this PPV was spot on and nearly saved the show.Other than that the usual suspects, Benoit, Christian, Melina, showed up to try and save the show, but like so many other Smackdown PPVs it's going to get a no vote from me. The Hardcore Holly vs. Mr. Kennedy match was filled with stiff wrestling and missed spots. They also used the opening match to crap all over the legacy that is the Legion of Doom. I don't know what was more of an abomination: Heidenreich pretending to be Hawk, or the size of Animal's gut. Simon Dean gave a very mediocre comedy act, then spent the night eating hamburgers (which grew very old by the end). The announcers were, as always, way too eager to give away the match endings by very enthusiastically proclaiming the opposite to be true. Still, feel free to avoid this PPV. ***

reviewText: This PPV began a 3 PPV streak of SmackDown coming out with good PPV's which is really something to say since WWE puts more effort & energy into RAW.1. Animal, Heidenrich, Christy Hemme vs. MNM - Honestly, this was the best the team of Animal & Heidenrich (I REFUSE TO CALL THEM "LEGION OF DOOM"!) looked during their whole run.  It was a nice opener between the three.  This was Hemme's best WWE match as well.Lashley vs. Simon Dean - We all know Simon Dean is just a glorified jobber so we already knew who was going over in this squash match but at least they made it entertaining by having Dean eat 20 hamburgers in backstage skits thoughout the show.U.S. Champion Chris Benoit vs. Booker T vs. Orlando Jordan vs. Christian - It was a nice match but nothing really memorable except start to set up the Benoit/Booker fued...once again, Christian does the job.  (And you wonder why he headed to TNA a month later)Rey Mysterio vs. J.B.L. - Great match between these two from start to finish.Casket Match: Undertaker vs. Cowboy Bob & Randy Orton - Another great match with some comedic spots.  However, the ending really killed it since it's something we've already seen before.Crusierweight Champion Nunzio vs. Juventud - Decent match at best but how do you expect to follow up Undertaker being set on fire?World Champion Batista vs. Eddie Guerrero - This was more about "putting over a storyline" than having a great match because Eddie was putting over the storyline of "not lying, cheating, and stealing."  The match was good but again, nothing really memorable besides the fact that this was the last we'll see of Eddie Guerrero on WWE PPV.DVD extras include The Orton's looking in the casket after it burned, Eric Bischoff visiting backstage, and Simon Dean ordering the 20 cheeseburgers before the PPV (very funny)I recommend.
summary: Eddie Guerrero's Last PPV...along with Christian's

reviewText: No Mercy was an overall good PPV! It whiped the floor with unforgiven seeing as Unforgiven only had two really good matches (Carlito vs. Flair and Hardy vs. Edge)! It only had a few stinkers, so let's begin!Match #1 MNM vs. LOD & Christy: This sucked so bad I'm not even going to count it towards the score! The new LOD needs to stop winning matches cuz they suck...needless to say the wrong people won this match...Match #2 Bobby Lashley vs. Simon Dean: What a squash!!! Such a squash that it was over in less then two minutes, but I still liked it. Lashley almost pulled off this sick spot by trying to throw Dean backwards off the turnbuckle and catch him in the position to do his finisher...but unfortunately it was slightly botched. Lashley then hits his finisher on Dean, and Dean has to keep on his promise of eating 20 double cheeseburgers. 8/10Match #3 Chris Benoit (c) vs. Christian vs. Orlando Jordan vs. Booker T Fatal-4-Way for the United States Championship: Benoit got a bigger pop here then the hometown boy Booker T!!! GREAT MATCH! If it went another 5 minutes I would have put this as match of the night, but it was just too short! Great performances by everyone here!!! Benoit makes Christian tap to the Sharpshooter and retains! 10/10 eventhough it was short...Match #4 Hardcore Holly vs. Mr. Kennedy: Kennedy got a clean pinfall here, which surprised me, but it made him look good and Holly did his job! Pretty good match! It just sucks Holly is used to job to new talent all the time, but hopefully he'll get a decent push before his career is over. Sylvan comes out and attacks Holly after the match for no apparent reason...it made no sense. Anyways yeah, Kennedy wins! 8/10Match #5 JBL vs. Rey Mysterio: Match of the night right here!!! I was so into this match, it was crazy! JBL and Rey have great chemistry and David & Goliath was really portrayed well here. Surprisingly, Jillian Hall's interference was kept very minimal. And just as you think Rey is gonna win, JBL ducks the West Coast Pop and nails Rey with a Clothesline From Hell!!! The Wrestling GOD WINS!!! 10/10!!!Match #6 Undertaker vs. The Ortons in a Handi-cap Casket Match: Another AWESOME match! I thought this was gonna stink the joint out with Bob Orton in there, but how wrong I was! Bob Orton in action was kept to a minimum here, and that was a good thing. Late in the match, Randy and Taker went one on one and tore it up!!! Bob Orton closes the casket with Randy and Taker inside, but the refs don't call for the bell because both Ortons needed to be out. Finally Randy catches Undertaker with a vile chair shot behind and closes the casket for the Orton's VICTORY! Afterwards, Randy chops a hole in the casket, pours gasoline all over it, and lights it on fire!!! Great ENDING!!! 10/10Match #7 Juvi w/ The Mexicools vs. Nunzio (c) w/ Vito for the Cruiserweight Championship: This was good, high paced action! Short and sweet! The Mexicools kept Vito at bay, while Juvi hit Nunzio with some sort of Piledriver/Shoulderbreaker move to finish him off...it looked like it really hurt! Juvi is the new Cruiserweight CHAMP!!! 8/10Match #8 Batista (c) vs. Eddie Guererro for the World Heavyweight Championship: I don't care what anyone says, but this was good! Eddie pulled a good wrestling match out of Batista, and that's all that mattered! Eddie put in some really great offense and eventhough you knew Batista was gonna win, Eddie really looked like he had a chance. Eddie teases some chair shots but pulls back the urge to hit Batista. Batista catches him a few times and gets really pissed! Batista hits Eddie with a Spinebuster and then goes for the Batista Bomb, but Eddie reverses it with a Sunset Flip into a pin attempt. Eddie then goes for the Frogsplash and misses, but runs right into another Spinebuster and Batista retains his title! At the end they shake hands, but when Batista turns away Eddie makes an evil smirk towards him, then he turns around suspecting Eddie may cheap shot him! As Eddie leaves, Batista celebrates some more as No Mercy comes to a close. 9/10!No Mercy 2005 gets a 63/70 which is an A!!! If you see this PPV, skip the opener and jump right into Bobby Lashley vs. Simon Dean!!! You'll really enjoy this show!
summary: Good one for the Brand in Blue!

reviewText: On a sad note, Eddie Guerrero passed away on Sunday, November 13, 2005. This review will mark his last pay per view match. This is also the last ppv dvd cover he is on. I will miss Eddie. My prayers go out to his family and friends. He was one of the great ones not only in the ring  but in life. Eddie is in Heaven with his Lord & Saviour, Jesus Christ now. His testimony & legacy here on earth will live on & continue to affect & touch many lives.6 Person Tag Team MatchMNM vs L.O.D. & Christy Hemme 7/10- a good match to kick off the show. these 2 teams work well together. reminds me of old school tag team wrestling. even the women perform well. Melina's screaming is annoying but Christy has shown improvement in the ring.Eddie Guerrero wishes Batista good luck in the dresing room.Simon Dean vs Bobby Lashley(the loser has to eat 20 double cheeseburgers) 4/10- not a very good match. Lashley's debut is pitiful as he goofs his finishing manuever. Dean can't carry the big oaf well. WWE's plans to make Lashley into a black Brock Lesnar is failing.Smackdown's newest guy, Steve Romero, interviews JBL & Jillian Hall. they are interupted by Rey Mysterio.United States ChampionshipFatal Four WayChris Benoit vs Booker T(w/ Sharmell) vs Orlando Jordan vs Christian 9/10- the best match of the night. even Jordan is made to look good. fast paced action that goes back & forth. this one steals the show.funny backstage segment: Simon Dean & Bobby Lashley.Mr. Kennedy vs Hardcore Holly 3.5/10- the worst match of the night. Kennedy is trying to be a cross between The Rock & The Road Dogg in personality. He is an "A" #1 dork! these 2 don't work well together. BORING!Sharmell confronts Booker T & they are interrupted by Mr. Kennedy backstage.John Bradshaw Layfield(w/ Jillian Hall) vs Rey Mysterio 8.5/10- David vs Goliath! these 2 put on a good match. a classic big guy vs little guy. they work well together in the ring.Handicap Casket MatchOrtons vs Undertaker 8/10- a better match than i anticipated. Cowboy Bob does well for an old man. back forth action makes it intense at times. a great ending.WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipNunzio(w/ Vito) vs Juventud(w/ Super Crazy) 8/10- a very good matchup of little guys. these 2 go all out. WWE needs to rebuild the cruiserweights back up. match should have been given more time.World Heavyweight ChampionshipBatista vs Eddie Guerrero 8/10- Eddie carries Batista well in this one. back & forth action that carries a lot of sentimentality now that Eddie is gone. i watched this match that night after Eddie passed away. Guerrero is tempted to cheat several times during the match but restrains himself. great ending to the match & in the aftermath. October 9 was Eddie's birthday.some good extras with Simon Dean at a fast food drive thru on his little scooter. Teddy long confronts Eric Bischoff backstage.EDDIE GUERREROOCTOBER 9,1967-NOVEMBER 13,2005see you in Heaven one day, Eddie!

reviewText: 1.6 man tag match- Nice way to open the show. A short match but some fast paced action. 7/102 Lashley vs Simon Dean- Lashley is looking impressive. A short match and a dominant match. 6.5/103. Fatal Four Way- A very fast paced match. This was the last PPV match that Christian wrestled in the WWE. Nice work by all competitors. 9/104. Ken Kennedy...... Kennedy vs Hardcore Holly- Kennedy is also impressing me. He has great mic skills and could be a world champion someday. His finisher is great and unique. Kinda boring match but it's not bad. 5/105. JBL vs Rey Mysterio- Both men put on good performances. Rey did his usual good job against a big guy and JBL did a good job with the power. 8/106. Handicap Casket Match- I wished there were more weapons used. Although the weapons that were used were used well. I am glad that Orton won to continue being the Legend Killer. 8.5/107 Nunzio vs Juventud- Nice fast paced match. Some hard hitting moves. Both men did a good job.  9/108. Batista vs Eddie Guerrero- Best match of the night. I like the parts when Eddie wanted to cheat. It made the fans thinking that it was the old eddie. Unfortunately this was Eddie's last PPV match. Eddie you will be missed. I send my condolences to Eddie's family and friends. 9.5/10 R.I.P Eddie GuerreroOverall this was a good PPV. It had a lot of good to great matches. I  think everyone should see this movie because it was Eddie's last PPV. The WWE will not be the same without Eddie. God Bless you Eddie.

reviewText: Benoit vs. OJ vs. Christian vs. BookerVery refreshing fatal fourway that was definitely the best US title match in a while and probably of the whole year. Also good to see Benoit retainRATING: 84/100Mysterio vs. JBLDecent match which had too much of JBL to make this a big hit, a few Mysterio moves were good but enough to make this match stand out.RATING: 70/100Kennedy vs. Hardcore HollyProbably slightly better than expected and had a few nearfalls which was good to watch. There was the typical Holly offense which gets quite boring after seeing it so many times. Holly didn't raise Kennedy here which made for a stale to upper stale match.RATING: 67/100MNM vs. LODA very entertaining tag match as Christy was exciting to watch and there were some good tag moments. The ending was unexpected and a nice touch that raised the rating to a 70RATING: 70/100Lashley vs. Simon DeanNot bad. Dean has a lot more potential than he has been displaying so he could really be good in future with a better gimmick. Lashley's power was very impressive and shows that he has a bright future. Overall, it was basically just jobber match though, which I don't particularly enjoy.RATING: 60/100Undertaker vs. Randy & Bob OrtonProbably the biggest letdown of the night as I was expecting so much from this and thought that it would steal the show. Unfortunately, there were far too few chain wrestling, counters and innovative weapon use for this match to be successful. It lacked the spark of Orton & Takers other 2 matches, and I believe that it was Bob Orton that killed the spark as they could have worked so much more innovatively without his hindrance.Obviously an Undertaker win would have helped this matchRATING: 79/100Juventud vs. NunzioAnother successful cruiserweight match that was exciting and high-flying for the full 7min period. As usual I am not too happy about the time that they allowed for this as double digits would have definitely worked better.Very exciting well done matchRATING: 82/100Batista vs. eddie GuerreroBetter than expected and it had good psychology with mini moments including Eddie wondering he should cheat or not. I found this match very exciting and was always intrigued to see what was going to happen next.RATING: 86/10075% - A good PPV that won't be remembered for too long but was overall definitely a solid show.

reviewText: Predictions for Announced MatchesWORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP- Batista (C) vs. Eddie GuererroThis is a tough one to pick because it seems like a great angle for Eddie to win it and set up a rivalry with Benoit.  But all signs show Orton vs. Batista for the title.  Signs know show Batista winning but a rematch at survivor series. Maybe a eddie turn where he gets dq'ed. Please not another dq.My Prediction: BatistaUNITED STATES TITLE- FATAL FOUR-WAYFor me I only see two people winning this match; Christian and Chris Benoit. I hope Christian wins because he would make a great champ and I'm dying to see a Benoit and Eddie angle. IfChristian or Booker T win then look for Batista to lose. Orlando doesn't have a prayer.  There could be many rivalrys as a result of this. Not many spoilers showing this one. I hope that means a title change.My Prediction: Chris BenoitHANDICAP CASKET MATCH- Randy and Cowboy Bob Orton vs. UndertakerI can't wait for this match. We got the king of the casket match vs. the LEGEND KILLER. The WWE wants to give Orton a push so he has to get the best of this rivalry. This rivalry will be intact after NO MERCY. Look for an Orton win or a controversial Undertaker win. This will be Bob's last match for sure. I am glad this is a casket match because they're awesome and the finale can be hell in a cell or buried alive.My Prediction: The Ortons (IT'S HIS DESTINY)JBL vs. Rey MysterioYou've got the fan's favorite wrestler who never loses at PPVs vs. the WWE's favorite wrestler who is always in the main event. Look for JBL to win this so they can solidfy another push after Batista gives up the title. The only way he'll  face Batista again is Elimination Chamber. That rivalry is over used.My Prediction: JBL (THE WRESTLING GOD)L.O.D and Christy vs. MNMI wish this was a title match without the girls but should be entertaining because the rivalry has become so heated. I'm having a hard time deciding this one because MNM needs to win so they'll still be contenders and top dawgs on Smackdown. But LOD and Christy are the fan favorites.My Prediction: L.O.D and Christy (Don't worry MNM will still be contenders after No Mercy)Bobby Lashley vs. Simon DeanBobby looks very impressive. He'll get title shots after he has enough matches against heels like Dean. The WWE will put Bobby next agianst better competition like Raw did with Masters. This one will be ugly. I hope Bobby's good on the mike.My Prediction: Bobby LashleyPredicted Matches for NO MERCY 2005CRUISERWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIPNunzio(C) vs. JuventudThis match could be Juventud instead of London but Paul gets the edge because he has been in more matches. They need an excited match to get more fans for this divisionMy Prediction: JuviHardcore Holly vs. Ken KennedyKen will win whoever he wrestles because the good heels have matches and they want to save his first loss for a good wrestler, like Raw did with Matthews. I just hope the less significant matches are excited so the whole PPV is awesome.My Prediction: Ken KennedyLooks like this will be an awesome PPV, at least the best Smackdown ppv of the year. But I said the same thing about The Great American Bash. All I'm asking for are new champions. Please! Smackdown finally looks like it's going in the right direction. The WWE has to realize these better ratings have to do with the new contenders. Christian, Orton, and Guerrero deserve their pushes. The WWE lost viewers in the last ppvs because they sucked. I've got a good feeling about this one.

reviewText: This wasn't the best No Mercy, but it was really good.1.6 Man Tag Team MatchLOD and Christy Hemme vs. MNMThis was an OK match, but it wasn't good for an opener. It was too slow. Watchable, but you won't be watching it more than once.6 out of 10.2.Simon Dean vs. Lashley(Loser must eat 20 double cheeseburgers)This was an incredibly bad match. This is something that you would find on Velocity. Incredibly short as well. I guess I'll add a point because seeing Dean eating 20 double cheeseburgers is pretty funny.3 out of 10.3.Fatal Four Way MatchChris Benoit vs. Christian vs. Booker T vs. Orlando Jordan(WWE US Championship)This was a really good match. No crazy moves, just straight up wrestling. There were good use of submissions in this one, along with everybody getting into the fight instead of having 2 people go at it for a long time.9 out of 10.4.Mr. Kennedy vs. Hardcore HollyThis was a good, solid match. Mr. Kennedy is a good wrestler and so is Hardcore, so on paper this matchup looked pretty good, and it was.7 out of 10.5.JBL vs. Rey MysterioThis was a really good match. There were some really impressive moves such as a bulldog to the outside from the apron and I really liked the way the match ended.9 out of 10.6.Handicap Casket MatchThe Undertaker vs. Cowboy Bob Orton and Randy OrtonThis was a very good match. You'd think that the addition of Bob Orton it would be bad, but it actually helped. This was the best casket match I have seen(I've yet to see the Royal Rumble 1998 casket match but I heard that it was really good.) Speaking of that match, they used the same "fire" storyline after the match was over. This match just barely earns a perfect score.10 out of 10.7.Juventud vs. Nunzio(WWE Cruiserweight Championship)This was a good Cruiserweight title match. Had a few good high-flying moves, but not too many. All I can say is that it was good.7 out of 10.8.Eddie Guerrero(R.I.P.) vs. Batista(World Heavyweight Championship)This was Eddie Guerrero's last PPV match and last really good match.Eddie was a much better opponent for Batista than JBL because he's quicker.The middle of this match was slow, with Eddie trying to hurt Batista's back.But the last few minutes were really good. I wasn't expecting the ending.8 out of 10.
summary: Started off slow, but picked up by the 3rd match

reviewText: No Mercy 2005 was the third ever match up between Randy Orton and The Undertaker on a ppv in the year of 2005. Chris Benoit defended his USA title for the first time on a ppv, and Batista defended the world heavyweight title for, get this, the FITH time. Not since JBL and Triple H has someone defended it that much."LOD" and Christy Hemme vs. MNM:Why couldn't this have been for the tag titles? We haven't seen a title defense for a Smackdown ppv or a combined ppv since GAB. Anyway this was okay for an opener, "LOD" has a good entrance pyro and Christy and Melina are as hot as ever. The action was smooth in most areas and "LOD" and Christy win after Christy gives the doomsday device to Melina for the pin. 7/10Bobby Lashley vs. Simon Dean:Can we say job fest? Dean didn't stand a damn chance. Bobby has potential for great heel status with his physique and I am hoping one day to see him tangle with Benoit. But until then this match wasn't that good. 3/10USA ChampionshipFatal FourwayChris Benoit [Champion] vs. Booker T vs. Christain vs. Orlando J:Best match of the night. Nothing but fast paced action all the way through. A lot of pin fall breaking up as all four men try to pin each other left and right. Benoit was a suplexing machine, first Orlando, then Christain, then Booker, what a match!The end has Benoit taking out both Orlando and Booker, then applying the sharpshooter to Christain and Christain taps. 9/10 [Great Match]Hardcore Holly vs. Mrrrrrr. Kennedy....Kennedy:Okay match, Kennedy has potential, at least I think so, to be a great future player in the business. Some actually good technical moves and Kennedy wins with his great finishing move. 6/10JBL vs. Rey Mysterio:This was actually a good match. The power and size of JBL meets the agility and speed of Rey Mysterio. Lots of faced past action by Rey and JBL even trips Rey on the steel steps and Rey's face bounces onto the steel steps. JBL even gives a falloway slam off the top rope to Mysterio!The ending comes after Mysterio hits the 619 and goes for the West Coast Pop but JBL moves and hits the clothesline from Hell for the win. 7.5/10The Undertaker vs. Randy Orton and Cowboy Bob OrtonHandicap Casket Match:Heres to hoping to see a HIAC match at Armageddon. Both Randy and The UT have good chemistry together and this is their second best match so far, my opinion. UT nailed Randy in the back with a steel chair and then Bob sprays a fire extinguisher into Taker's face.The end comes when Randy nails Taker in the head with a steel chair and both Orton's put Taker into the casket. 8.5/10After the match both Orton's light the casket on fire with Taker still inside it, or so it seemed......Crusierweight ChampionshipJuventude vs. Nunzio [Champion]:This match was just put on so the crowd could calm down for the main event. It's nice to see the Mexicools back on a ppv. Juventude wins with what's called the Juvi Driver and becomes crusierweight champ. 7/10World Heavyweight ChampionshipBatista [Champion] vs. Eddie Guerrero:Good match, but hopefully the next time they face each other it will be a special stipulation match. Guerrero even had a few cheers for him. Highlights include Guerrero thinking over whether to use a steel chair or not as Batista was down, then decides against using it. Batista also uses big man power moves to combat Guerrero's technical moves.The ending has Batista giving a huge spinebuster to Guerrero for the pin. 8/10 [Okay match, but the next should be better]I reccomend this for the Fatal Four Way match, the Casket Match, and the World title with Guerrero using great facial expressions as he and Batista continue to like each other.Other than that the crowd enthusiasm was a little dissapointing, and a lot of jobber matches brought it down. Other than that this was a solid ppv.
